P(X\geq kY)
\displaystyle P(X\geq kY)=P(Y\leq X/k)=\sum_{r=1}^{\infty}P(Y\leq r, X=rk)=\sum_{r=1}^{\infty}P(Y\leq r)P(X=rk)
P(Y\leq r)=\displaystyle\sum_{u=1}^{r}\frac{1}{2^{u}}= 1-\frac{1}{2^{r}}
P(X\geq kY)=\displaystyle \sum_{r=1}^{\infty} (1-\frac{1}{2^{r}})\frac{1}{2^{rk}}=\frac{2^k}{(2^k-1)(2^{k+1}-1)}
P(X\geq kY)=\displaystyle\frac{2}{2^{k+1}-1}
\displaystyle P(X\geq kY)=\sum_{r=1}^{\infty}P(X\geq kr,Y=r)
k=2
